description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1675-1680

  from_radio_id = adapter->from_radio_id + 1U;
  packet = (struct lichen_meshtastic_text_packet){
      .from = event->from,
      .to = event->to,
      .id = event->has_id ? event->id : from_radio_id,
      ...
  };

If adapter->from_radio_id starts at 0 (initial state), from_radio_id becomes 1, which is fine.

But the packet.id is set to either event->id (if provided) or from_radio_id. If event->has_id is false and from_radio_id is used, then adapter->from_radio_id is incremented (line 1700):
  adapter->from_radio_id = from_radio_id;

But if event->has_id is TRUE, from_radio_id is computed but not used, and adapter->from_radio_id is STILL incremented.

This means from_radio_id counter always increments even when the value isn't used, causing unnecessary ID consumption. Not a functional bug, but wasteful.
